verses.text: O \w come|strong="H3212"\w*, let us \w sing|strong="H7442"\w* unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: let us make a joyful \w noise|strong="H7321"\w* to the \w rock|strong="H6697"\w* of our \w salvation|strong="H3468"\w*.

Let us \w come|strong="H6923"\w* before his \w presence|strong="H6440"\w* with \w thanksgiving|strong="H8426"\w*, and make a joyful \w noise|strong="H7321"\w* unto him with \w psalms|strong="H2158"\w*.\f + \fr 95.2 \ft come…: Heb. prevent his face\f*

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* a \w great|strong="H1419"\w* \w God|strong="H0410"\w*, and a \w great|strong="H1419"\w* \w King|strong="H4428"\w* above all \w gods|strong="H0430"\w*.

In his \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* \add are\add* the deep \w places|strong="H4278"\w* of the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w*: the \w strength|strong="H8443"\w* of the \w hills|strong="H2022"\w* \add is\add* his also.\f + \fr 95.4 \ft In…: Heb. In whose\f*\f + \fr 95.4 \ft the strength…: or, the heights of the hills are his\f*

The \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* \add is\add* his, and he \w made|strong="H6213"\w* it: and his \w hands|strong="H3027"\w* \w formed|strong="H3335"\w* the \w dry|strong="H3006"\w* \add land\add*.\f + \fr 95.5 \ft The sea…: Heb. Whose the sea is\f*

O \w come|strong="H0935"\w*, let us \w worship|strong="H7812"\w* and bow \w down|strong="H3766"\w*: let us \w kneel|strong="H1288"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our \w maker|strong="H6213"\w*.

For he \add is\add* our \w God|strong="H0430"\w*; and we \add are\add* the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* of his \w pasture|strong="H4830"\w*, and the \w sheep|strong="H6629"\w* of his \w hand|strong="H3027"\w*. To \w day|strong="H3117"\w* if ye will \w hear|strong="H8085"\w* his \w voice|strong="H6963"\w*,

\w Harden|strong="H7185"\w* not your \w heart|strong="H3824"\w*, as in the \w provocation|strong="H4808"\w*, \add and\add* as \add in\add* the \w day|strong="H3117"\w* of \w temptation|strong="H4531"\w* in the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w*:\f + \fr 95.8 \ft provocation: Heb. contention\f*
When your \w fathers|strong="H0001"\w* \w tempted|strong="H5254"\w* me, \w proved|strong="H0974"\w* me, and \w saw|strong="H7200"\w* my \w work|strong="H6467"\w*.

\w Forty|strong="H0705"\w* \w years|strong="H8141"\w* long was I \w grieved|strong="H6962"\w* with \add this\add* \w generation|strong="H1755"\w*, and \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, It \add is\add* a \w people|strong="H5971"\w* that do \w err|strong="H8582"\w* in their \w heart|strong="H3824"\w*, and they have not \w known|strong="H3045"\w* my \w ways|strong="H1870"\w*:

Unto whom I \w sware|strong="H7650"\w* in my \w wrath|strong="H0639"\w* that they should not \w enter|strong="H0935"\w* into my \w rest|strong="H4496"\w*.\f + \fr 95.11 \ft that…: Heb. if they enter into my rest\f*
